    </div>

    <h2>Upstream License Inheritance</h2>
    <p>As a Linux distribution, Linxira OS inherits license obligations from upstream projects. Key dependencies:</p>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Component</th><th>Upstream Project</th><th>License</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Base System</td><td><a href="https://ubuntu.com">Ubuntu</a> / <a href="https://linuxmint.com">Linux Mint</a></td><td>GPL-2.0+ / various</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Desktop</td><td><a href="https://kde.org">KDE Plasma</a></td><td>GPL-2.0+</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Installer</td><td><a href="https://calamares.io">Calamares</a></td><td>GPL-3.0+</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Kernel</td><td><a href="https://kernel.org">Linux Kernel</a></td><td>GPL-2.0</td></tr>
      <tr><td>GNU Tools</td><td><a href="https://gnu.org">GNU Project</a></td><td>GPL-2.0+ / LGPL-2.0+</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Firefox</td><td><a href="https://mozilla.org">Mozilla</a></td><td>MPL-2.0</td></tr>
      <tr><td>LibreOffice</td><td><a href="https://documentfoundation.org">The Document Foundation</a></td><td>MPL-2.0</td></tr>
    </table>

    <h2>GPL Copyleft Explanation</h2>
    <p>The GNU General Public License (GPL) has <strong>copyleft</strong> provisions: if you distribute software containing GPL code, your derivative work must also be GPL-licensed.</p>

    <p>Impact on Linxira OS:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>All custom code we distribute must be open source (already GPL-3.0)</li>
      <li>Users running Linxira OS locally are not subject to copyleft restrictions</li>
      <li>Users creating derivative distributions must comply with upstream licenses</li>
      <li>User customizations and scripts are not subject to copyleft (unless they include GPL code)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Non-Free Components</h2>
    <p>Linxira OS may include the following non-free components:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Firmware</strong>: Some hardware requires proprietary firmware</li>
      <li><strong>GPU Drivers</strong>: NVIDIA drivers are proprietary</li>
      <li><strong>User-Optional</strong>: VS Code, Chrome, etc. are proprietary</li>
    </ul>
    <p>These components are user-installed by choice; Linxira OS does not mandate non-free software.</p>

